The paper deals with communication schemes involving channel estimation and feedback, which are topics typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also considers a multiple-input single-output system, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of multiple antennas for beamforming and data transmission is a common technique in Multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Finally, the paper discusses the design of variable-rate quantizers, which is a topic relevant to Communication (cs.COM) sub-category.
